How to find the unique id of a server member
As a Technical Moderator, you may want to ban a server member. You can do this via a script. Prior to this, you must find the unique id of the server member.
To find the unique id of the server member:
1.	Log in to Discord.
2.	Navigate to User Settings. User Settings is represented by a gear icon at the bottom of the left-hand side of the page.
3.	In the page that is displayed, from the left-hand menu, select Advanced.
4.	Toggle the Developer Mode to On.
5.	Close the window.
6.	From the left-hand menu, click the Discover icon.
7.	Click Servers.
8.	From the list of Featured Servers, right-click a Server.
9.	Click the option, Copy Server ID.
